4.
the functions we used fork(),exec(),wait();
wait() causes the parent process to wait until the child process finishes execution.
fork() Creates a new child process by duplicating the parent process.
exec() Replaces the current process with a new program.
Start
Create child process using fork()
If Child Process
  Execute another program using exec()
Else
  Wait for child process using wait()
  Print "Parent Process Resumed"
Stop
and then prints Parent Process Resumed.
CODE
#include <stdio.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <sys/wait.h>
int main()
{
 if(fork()==0)
execl("/bin/ls","ls",NULL);
 else
    {
 wait(NULL);
printf("Parent Resumed\n");
    }
}

